  "statement": {
    "ambiguity_status": "clear",
    "intended": "For $k\\geq 0$ and $n\\geq 1$ let $v(n,k)$ count the prime factors of $n+k$ which do not divide $n+i$ for $0\\leq i<k$. Equivalently, $v(n,k)$ counts the number of prime factors of $n+k$ which are $>k$.\n\nIs it true that\\[v_0(n)=\\max_{k\\geq 0}v(n,k)\\to \\infty\\]as $n\\to \\infty$?",
